      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Nor Turistväg - Gamle Strynefjellevegen</name>
        <description><![CDATA[The old roadway between east and west is a museum experience in itself. It is a historic alternative to the new trunk road across Strynefjellet Mountain.<br><br>Built by manual labour towards the end of the 19th century, this road conveys a historical narrative. The road is an attraction in itself and a testimony to a masterpiece of engineering design from a bygone time. <br><br>Old hand-built walls of meticulously cut stones and long rows of guard stones characterise the stretch of road across the mountain. The scenic route between Eastern and Western Norway was listed as a protected road in 2009.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#line-FF5252-3000</styleUrl>
